		<td><b>PPU rendering, MMC2 and the 34th tile fetch</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />When the PPU fetches the 34th tile at the end of the scanline, from where does it fetch it?  How does that concept fit into Loopy's scrolling doc?  That is, from which nametable does the 34th tile come from?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sat Jan 10, 2015 7:29 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: PPU rendering, MMC2 and the 34th tile fetch</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The 34th tile is one tile to the right of the 33rd tile. It comes from the same nametable as the 33rd tile unless the 33rd tile is rightmost on its nametable.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


